The Cross River State governor, Ben Ayade, has defected to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). Ayade announced his decision on Thursday morning during a meeting with six APC governors at the Government House in Calabar. The governors were led by the national caretaker chairman of the APC and Yobe State governor, Mai Mala Buni, who was accompanied by Kebbi, Imo, Plateau, Ekiti and Jigawa State governors.  READ:Â  LG Polls: APC Chieftain Lauds Ayade, Commends CROSIEC